 258. The purpose of this work is to improve Schwartz’s edition both in recensio and constitution of the text. About what concerns the recensio, this was extended to sixteen manuscripts instead of the four used by Schwartz. The reassessment involved not only the more recent manuscripts but also some witnesses dating to the Palaeologan age, disregarded or only partially collated by the former editor.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn Italian.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aEuripides.  aHippolytus.  aScholia.  aTriclinius.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2016 Part 1z978311076250108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070100508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2016z9783110485097oZDB-23-DGD0 cEPUBz97831104706730 cprintz978311046861840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311047139740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110471397423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110471397/original  a978-3-11-070100-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2016b2016  a978-3-11-076250-1  DG Plus DeG Package 2016 Part 1b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGDb2016  aZDB-23-DGGb2016